subSubSection.paragraph:
Lateral sense organs present on all chaetigers, located between notopodia and neuropodia, just posterior to notopodial postchaetal lobes; elliptical with irregularly clustered pores in middle part of branchial region, straight line-shaped with regularly clustered pores from posterior part of branchial region to end of body (
Fig. 11B, D
); with 17–20 pores (long axis: 5–6 μm) in branchial region, with 28–30 pores (length of lateral sense organ: 10.5–11 μm) in posterior region.
